Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Roughly chop the @exotic mushroom mix{125%g}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the onion and mushrooms to the pan and fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Use a #fork{} to roughly mash the beans in a #bowl{}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} to the pan and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the mashed beans, @ketchup{1%sachet} and a splash of @water{}.

Mix together and allow to warm through. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Lay the @tortillas{8} on a #board{}, spoon an even amount of the bean filling down the centre of each, then fold in half.

Drizzle a little oil into the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{} then lay in the tacos, still folded (pack them snugly together with the open side facing up).

Top each taco with @grated cheese{50%g}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @tomato{1}(cut into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks.

Chop the @scallion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced) into 4 wedges.

Mix the tomato and scallion in a bowl then season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @lime{1}(cut into wedges) juice—all to taste.

Halve the @avocado{1}.

Use a spoon to scoop out the flesh into a bowl.

Roughly mash with a fork.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lime juice.

Once cooked, remove the tacos from the oven.

Serve in the oven dish and allow everyone to help themselves.

Spoon tomato salsa and smashed avocado on top.

Finish with a squeeze of lime juice.